President Obama called Colorado Governor John Hickenlooper and Colorado Springs Mayor Steve Bach to receive an update on the damaging fires in Colorado. The President expressed concern about the extent of damage to homes in the Colorado Springs area and plans to visit the area on Friday to view the damage and thank the responders. The administration is focused on bringing all resources to assist local responders in Colorado and other Western States impacted by fires. Federal support is also being provided to officials battling fires in Alaska, Arizona, California, Montana, Nevada, New Mexico, Utah, and Wyoming. The President asked for any additional resources that could be provided and expressed his thoughts and prayers for responders and families impacted by the fires.